  <Summary>Thoth-Amon wields their arcane power against Conan and Chabela!

*Contents*
"King Thoth-Amon" - continues the adaptation of Lin Carter and L. Sprague de Camp's novel "Conan the Buccaneer". Adapted by Roy Thomas, John Buscema and Tony DeZuniga.
~"The most mysterious, most dangerous sorcerer alive - king of a mighty sea-going empire? Aye, unless Conan the BUccaneer has his way!"~
"Notes on Various Peoples of the Hyborian Age" - an essay by Robert E. Howard with illustrations by Ernie Chan and Anton Caravana
"The Deadly Claws of Kathulos" - a review of books by Fred Blosser
"Pass of Death" - concludes the adaptation of "Kings of the Night". Adapted by Roy Thomas and David Wenzel
a frontispiece pin-up by Tony DeZuniga</Summary>
